<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.users.uswest.net/~brattsyblu/tmboots.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
And the next step in the newbie Quest results in this...<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.users.uswest.net/~brattsyblu/machete.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
All in all the newbie armors are really very well done.  I know alot of people just pretty much twink the heck out of their chars but these armors are a nice step for those starting from scratch and a nice step before the Etched Ivy mid level armor quests.  Definately a good Risk Vs. Reward.<br>
<br>
The Blade however is severly lacking.  It requires killing about ~30 orc lumberjacks (uncommon spawn) if not more, then buyng enough sharpening stones to be able to sharpen the blade before hand in.  Considering you can buy a 4/22 sword for ~2pp from a vendor in RV the reward was a let down.  Basically it's alot of uncommon rare drop farming and you could easily earn the 2pp just trying to gather the components for teh blade to go buy the vendor bought one rather than finishing the quest.<br>
<br>
PS- I havn't done the legs or the sleeves yet, as I havn't seen the scale required for them drop.  I could just be very unlucky though, took me awhile to get the bat piece for the BP.<br>
<br>
